A barracouta is a type of fish found in the temperate southern hemisphere. 
It has a long, slender body with a pointed head and sharp teeth. 
The color of a barracouta varies, but it is usually silver or gray with darker markings on the back. 
The skin of a barracouta is smooth and its scales are small and difficult to see. 
Barracouta are most commonly found in coastal waters, but can also be found in deeper offshore waters. 
They are an important food fish and are often caught for commercial purposes. 
Barracouta are also popular among recreational anglers.
